    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-01-20T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-01-20T04:00:00-05:00" n="398"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d398">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.2221/179: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Havre</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wiley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Havre</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-01-20T09:00:00+00:00"
                            >January 20, 1937—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Forty persons, of whom 20 American citizens recruited in the United States for
                    Spanish Government forces, disembarked from steamship <hi rend="italic"
                        >Lafayette</hi> 18th and about 100 expected to arrive steamship <hi
                        rend="italic">Paris</hi> 23rd. Will begin stamping “not valid for travel in
                    Spain” on all passports passengers disembarking not so stamped. Full report by
                    mail follows.<note n="26" xml:id="d398fn26">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wiley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
